-- Turkey banks association sees no sharp decline in 2014 bank profits 
-- By Ebru Tuncay
-- Thu Mar 13, 2014 05:39AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, March 13 (Reuters) - The Turkish Banking Association does not see a sharp decline in banking sector profits in 2014 as a whole after they tumbled in January, Chairman Huseyin Aydin told reporters on Thursday.

Turkish banking sector's net profit dropped 43.9 percent in January. [ID:nI7N0L208A] Credit growth is expected at 15-20 percent this year, Aydin said, adding that he expected the ratio of non-performing loans not to exceed 3 percent in 2014.